						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up in the barber's lane.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarāya A.D. 1547.</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of Sadāśivarāya is dated Śaka 1469, Plavaṁga, Āshāḍha śu. 11, Wednesday. But for the week day the details correspond to A.D. 1547, June 28. The weekday, however, was Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It records the remission of tax on barbers by the king in the Toṟugali-sīme at the instance of Mallōja and Chaṁdōja.</p>						

						</summary>
